Patch Set 3: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

(1 inline comment)

The patch doesn't work. When run it fails with 'oslo.config.cfg.DuplicateOptError: duplicate option: tcp_keepidle' on the code:
  File "glance/glance/cmd/pecan_api.py", line 59, in <module>
      CONF.register_opts(socket_opts)

The reason is that option 'tcp_keepidle' is already registered in common/wsgi.py. The traceback is following:
  File "glance/glance/cmd/pecan_api.py", line 30, in <module>
    import glance.store
  File "glance/glance/store/__init__.py", line 30, in <module>
    from glance.store import scrubber
  File "glance/store/scrubber.py", line 33, in <module>
    import glance.registry.client.v1.api as registry
  File "glance/registry/client/v1/api.py", line 29, in <module>
    from glance.registry.client.v1 import client
  File "glance/glance/registry/client/v1/client.py", line 28, in <module>
    from glance.registry.api.v1 import images
  File "glance/glance/registry/api/v1/__init__.py", line 20, in <module>
    from glance.common import wsgi
  File "glance/glance/common/wsgi.py", line 60, in <module>
    cfg.IntOpt('tcp_keepidle', default=600,

So the root cause is in import and usage of glance.store (lines 30, 76-77)

Hey,

Thanks a lot for the patch. I'd like to discuss a bit when it should land and whether swapping implementations of existing API versions is what we want to do.

I've sent an email to the m-l to discuss this. I'll block this patch until we reach some consensus there. Could you please join the discussion?

Please, don't let this -2 stop you from working on the patch. It's just to make sure we don't let this land until we all agree on the path we should follow.

Thanks again!
